# Geomodeling with GPR and Kriging

This repository implements a complete geomodeling pipeline using Gaussian Process Regression (GPR) and Kriging, applied to the SPE9 reservoir model. It includes:

- Log-transformed GPR for predicting permeability (`PERMX`)
- 5-fold cross-validation with inverse-scaling evaluation
- Benchmarking using Ordinary Kriging (2D)
- Visualization of prediction slices and uncertainty
- Export of predictions and uncertainty to Eclipse-compatible GRDECL files

## Features

- Real SPE9 grid data support via `load_spe9_data()`
- Log-transform to enforce non-negative predictions
- `StandardScaler` for stable GPR convergence
- Custom kernel: RBF + Matern (ν=1.5)
- Uncertainty (σ) exported alongside permeability
- Mid-slice visualization of input, prediction, and σ

## Outputs

- `PERMX_GPR.GRDECL`: predicted permeability in GRDECL format
- `SIGMA_GPR.GRDECL`: standard deviation (uncertainty) of predictions
- `gpr_prediction_slices.png`: side-by-side slice visualization

